{"id":43,"parent_id":34,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":43,"title":"Mark 9: \"Help Thou Mine Unbelief\"","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark 9: \"Help Thou Mine Unbelief\"","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief"},[".heading",{"id":"head10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.head10"},["h1","Mark 9"],[".subtitle","“Help Thou Mine Unbelief”"],[".intro","We learned in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/16"},"Matthew 16"],"that when Jesus and His disciples were at Caesarea Philippi He promised them, specifically Peter, the “keys of the kingdom of heaven” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/16.19"},"Matthew 16:19"],"). In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/17"},"Matthew 17"],"we read about the fulfillment of that promise on the Mount of Transfiguration.",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.1-13"},"Mark 9:1–13"],"also contains an account of that experience. After that sacred experience Peter, James, and John still needed to learn many things from the Master. As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9"},"Mark 9"],", look for ways He taught them and helped increase their faith and the faith and understanding of others as well. Although the plea in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.24"},"Mark 9:24"],"to “help thou mine unbelief” was from a father who desired help for his son, it might well be the plea of anyone who believes in the Savior but recognizes the need for more faith and knowledge."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f33","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f33"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-046-1.gif"}]],[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9"},"Mark 9"]],["p.para",{"id":"p207","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p207"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.2-32"},"Mark 9:2–32"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/17.1-23"},"Matthew 17:1–23"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/9.28-45"},"Luke 9:28–45"]],["p.para",{"id":"p208","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p208"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.33-50"},"Mark 9:33–50"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/18.1-9"},"Matthew 18:1–9"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/9.46-50"},"Luke 9:46–50"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f34","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f34"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9"},"Mark 9"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Transfigured"],"(v. 2)"],["td","A condition in which a person’s body is temporarily changed so he or she can endure the presence and glory of heavenly beings"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fuller"],"(v. 3)"],["td","A person whose business was making clothes clean and white"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Tabernacles"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Temporary shelters used for devotion and worship"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wist"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Knew"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Save"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Except"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Scribes"],"(vv. 11, 14, 16)"],["td","Men who taught the people the meaning of the law of Moses (see Bible Dictionary,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/scribe"},"“scribe,”"],"p. 770)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Set at nought"],"(v. 12)"],["td","Considered to be worthless or despised"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Saluted"],"(v. 15)"],["td","Greeted"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Hath a dumb spirit"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Cannot speak"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Pineth away"],"(v. 18)"],["td","Body became weak"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","The spirit tare him"],"(v. 20)"],["td","He went into convulsions"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Wallowed"],"(v. 20)"],["td","Fell down rolling around"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rent him sore"],"(v. 26)"],["td","He had severe convulsions"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Maimed"],"(v. 43)"],["td","Physically handicapped"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Quenched"],"(vv. 43–46, 48)"],["td","Put out"],["td"]]]]],[".",{"id":"f35","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f35"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-046-2.gif"}]],[".",{"id":"f36","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f36"},[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","Building a tabernacle"]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.2-13"},"Mark 9:2–13"],"—Jesus Is Transfigured on a High Mountain"],["p.para",{"id":"p225","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p225"},"See “Transfiguration, Mount of” in the Bible Dictionary (p. 786)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.43-48"},"Mark 9:43–48"],"—Cutting Off Your Hand or Foot, or Plucking out Your Eye"],["p.para",{"id":"p226","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p226"},"See “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/5.29-30"},"Matthew 5:29–30"],"(p. 14). The Joseph Smith Translation for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.40-48"},"Mark 9:40–48"],"(in the Bible appendix, pp. 804–5) also provides important insights on what Jesus meant in these verses."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.49-50"},"Mark 9:49–50"],"—Salt and Fire"],["p.para",{"id":"p227","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p227"},"Under the law of Moses, sacrifices were salted as a symbol of the lasting covenant between the Lord and His people. It made the sacrifice “good” to the Lord. Followers of Christ offer themselves as a living sacrifice to Him (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/omni/1.26"},"Omni 1:26"],"), which sacrifice brings the cleansing power of the Holy Ghost (or the baptism of fire)."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p228","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.p228"},"Do activity A or B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9"},"Mark 9"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Increasing Your Faith"],[".figure",{"id":"f37","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f37"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","In the story in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.14-29"},"Mark 9:14–29"],", what was the problem?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What did Jesus say about the problem? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.19,23,29"},"vv. 19, 23, 29"],")"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","What do you think the father meant by what he said to Jesus in verse 24?"]],["li",["span.label","4."],["p.para","How does this story help increase your faith or teach you how to increase your faith?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Learn from the Joseph Smith Translation"],[".figure",{"id":"f38","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-9-help-thou-mine-unbelief.f38"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Carefully read the Joseph Smith Translation for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/9.40-48"},"Mark 9:40–48"],". Who does it tell us that “thy hand,” “thy foot,” and “thine eye” symbolize?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Keeping in mind the explanations from the Joseph Smith Translation, how do you think this counsel could apply today to people your age?"]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
